13023     double h2[10];
13024     int ix;
13025     boolean_T exitg1;
13026   
13027     /* PREDICT Predict the label of an input given a trained neural network */
13028     /*    p = PREDICT(Theta1, Theta2, X) outputs the predicted label of X given the */
13029     /*    trained weights of a neural network (Theta1, Theta2) */
13030     /*  Useful values */
13031     /* num_labels = size(Theta2, 1); */
13032     /*  You need to return the following variables correctly  */
13033     /* p = zeros(size(X, 1), 1); */
13034     /* SIGMOID Compute sigmoid functoon */
13035     /*    J = SIGMOID(z) computes the sigmoid of z. */
13036     dv0[0] = 1.0;
13037     memcpy(&dv0[1], &X[0], 784U * sizeof(double));
13038     for (ixstart = 0; ixstart < 49; ixstart++) {
13039       mtmp = 0.0;
13040       for (itmp = 0; itmp < 785; itmp++) {
13041         mtmp += dv0[itmp] * b[itmp + 785 * ixstart];
13042       }
13043   
13044       x[ixstart] = -mtmp;
13045     }
13046   
13047     /* SIGMOID Compute sigmoid functoon */
13048     /*    J = SIGMOID(z) computes the sigmoid of z. */
13049     dv1[0] = 1.0;
13050     for (ixstart = 0; ixstart < 49; ixstart++) {
13051       dv1[ixstart + 1] = 1.0 / (1.0 + exp(x[ixstart]));
13052     }
13053   
13054     for (ixstart = 0; ixstart < 10; ixstart++) {
13055       mtmp = 0.0;
13056       for (itmp = 0; itmp < 50; itmp++) {
13057         mtmp += dv1[itmp] * b_b[itmp + 50 * ixstart];
13058       }
13059   
13060       h2[ixstart] = -mtmp;
13061     }
13062   
13063     for (ixstart = 0; ixstart < 10; ixstart++) {
13064       h2[ixstart] = 1.0 / (1.0 + exp(h2[ixstart]));
13065     }
13066   
13067     /* [dummy, p] = max(h2, [], 2); */
13068     ixstart = 1;
13069     mtmp = h2[0];
13070     itmp = 1;
13071     if (rtIsNaN(h2[0])) {
13072       ix = 2;
13073       exitg1 = false;
13074       while ((!exitg1) && (ix < 11)) {
13075         ixstart = ix;
13076         if (!rtIsNaN(h2[ix - 1])) {
13077           mtmp = h2[ix - 1];
13078           itmp = ix;
13079           exitg1 = true;
13080         } else {
13081           ix++;
13082         }
13083       }
13084     }
13085   
13086     if (ixstart < 10) {
13087       while (ixstart + 1 < 11) {
13088         if (h2[ixstart] > mtmp) {
13089           mtmp = h2[ixstart];
13090           itmp = ixstart + 1;
13091         }
13092   
13093         ixstart++;
13094       }
13095     }
13096   
13097     p = itmp;
13098

13100     return p;
